      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against in-vitro measurements from the FDA benchmark dataset across 5 operating points. Mean relative error was 12.4%, within the pre-specified 15% acceptance band. Power-law hemolysis model coefficients were calibrated against bovine blood at 37°C."
