      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for the primary quantity of interest (NIH) at the nominal operating point; Richardson extrapolation performed on at least three systematically refined meshes.",
      "rationale": "A mesh refinement study was conducted using three mesh densities: 4.2 M, 8.7 M, and 17.1 M polyhedral cells. The observed order of convergence for NIH was p = 1.3, and the fine-grid GCI was computed at 8.9%, which exceeds the 5% acceptance threshold. The assessment team noted that the high-shear impeller tip region exhibited oscillatory convergence between the medium and fine meshes, suggesting that the asymptotic range has not been fully achieved. Despite this, the team judged the discretization error acceptable given the conservative hemolysis model coefficients and proceeded with the medium mesh for production runs. The achieved level of 1 reflects that the formal GCI criterion was not satisfied; the required level for MRL 2 is 2.",
