      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions (turbulence model, hemolysis power law, Newtonian blood rheology) documented and justified for the flow regime and QoIs.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model was selected based on published comparisons for rotating machinery flows at similar Reynolds numbers. Newtonian blood rheology is appropriate at the shear rates encountered (>100 s^-1 throughout most of the flow domain). The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was applied with coefficients from Heuser and Opitz (1980), consistent with the validation dataset. Model form assumptions are documented in the model description report and supported by literature."
