    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team reviewed all 13 ASME V&V 40 factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were scoped as not required at MRL 2. Of the seven assessed factors, six met or exceeded their required levels. The discretization error factor achieved Level 1 against a required Level 2; however, the team judged this shortfall acceptable given the conservative hemolysis model calibration, the 8.9% GCI being only marginally above the 5% threshold, and the corroborating hydraulic performance validation results. The overall body of evidence is consistent with a Medium assurance level for the stated COU. The decision to accept the model for regulatory use was made on 2026-04-19.",
